{"serial": "12013", "department_serial": 13, "code": "EL3036", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Fiction into Film", "ch": "小說與電影"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Lin, Wen-Chi"], "ch": ["林文淇"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 5, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "A", "room": "116"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "英美語文學系", "en": "Department of English"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 5, "selected": 50, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "“1. 使學生熟悉短篇小說寫作；\n2. 使學生熟悉電影製作；\n3. 提高學生說故事的能力。“", "en": "“1. To familiarize students with short story writing.\n2. To familiarize students with film making.\n3. To cultivate students’ ability of story-telling.“"}, "outline": {"ch": "This course will introduce students to a variety of films adapted from short stories and novels. Students will read both the original texts and the films closely to get a comparative perspective of the literary and cinematic art of story-telling. Other than reading short stories, students should expect to watch films in the theater and on-line, answer questions before class every week, and be active in group discussions about the literary and film texts. Other requirements include one oral report, final exam, and final project. Attendance is mandatory.\nSyllabus:\nSept. 13 Introduction\nSept. 20 STRANGER THAN FICTION (2006)\nSept. 27 “Bringing Up Baby” / BRINGING UP BABY (1938)\nOct. 4 “The Killer“ / THE KILLER (1946)\nOct. 11 “The Swimmer” / THE SWIMMER (1957)\nOct. 18 “The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance“ / THE MAN WHO SHOT LIBERTY VALANCE (1962)\nOct. 25 〈母與子〉 / 母親三十歲 (1973)\nNov. 1 “The Fly“ / THE FLY (1986)\nNot. 8 “We can Remember It Wholesale“ / TOTAL RECALL (1990)\nNov. 15 “Jerry and Molly and Sam“  / SHORTCUTS  (1993)\nNov. 22 〈動物凶猛〉 / 陽光燦爛的日子 (1994)\nNov. 29  “Brokeback Mountain” / BROKEBACK MOUNTAIN (2005)\nDec. 6 “The Secret Life of Walter Mitty” / THE SECRET LIFE OF WALTER MITTY (2013)\nDec. 13 “Story of Your Life“ / THE ARRIVAL (2016)\nDec. 20 “Barn Burning”/ BURNING (2018)\nDec. 27 Final Report", "en": "This course will introduce students to a variety of films adapted from short stories and novels. Students will read both the original texts and the films closely to get a comparative perspective of the literary and cinematic art of story-telling. Other than reading short stories, students should expect to watch films in the theater and on-line, answer questions before class every week, and be active in group discussions about the literary and film texts. Other requirements include one oral report, final exam, and final project. Attendance is mandatory.\nSyllabus:\nSept. 13 Introduction\nSept. 20 STRANGER THAN FICTION (2006)\nSept. 27 “Bringing Up Baby” / BRINGING UP BABY (1938)\nOct. 4 “The Killer“ / THE KILLER (1946)\nOct. 11 “The Swimmer” / THE SWIMMER (1957)\nOct. 18 “The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance“ / THE MAN WHO SHOT LIBERTY VALANCE (1962)\nOct. 25 〈母與子〉 / 母親三十歲 (1973)\nNov. 1 “The Fly“ / THE FLY (1986)\nNot. 8 “We can Remember It Wholesale“ / TOTAL RECALL (1990)\nNov. 15 “Jerry and Molly and Sam“  / SHORTCUTS  (1993)\nNov. 22 〈動物凶猛〉 / 陽光燦爛的日子 (1994)\nNov. 29  “Brokeback Mountain” / BROKEBACK MOUNTAIN (2005)\nDec. 6 “The Secret Life of Walter Mitty” / THE SECRET LIFE OF WALTER MITTY (2013)\nDec. 13 “Story of Your Life“ / THE ARRIVAL (2016)\nDec. 20 “Barn Burning”/ BURNING (2018)\nDec. 27 Final Report"}, "textbook": {"ch": "Harrison, Stephanie. Adaptations: From Short Stories to Big Screen.  New York: Three Rivers Press, 2005.\nSelective films and excerpts of novels.", "en": "Harrison, Stephanie. Adaptations: From Short Stories to Big Screen.  New York: Three Rivers Press, 2005.\nSelective films and excerpts of novels."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100", "en": "100"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "1.Attendance and active participation (5 ％)\n2.Weekly journals and responses. (45 ％)\n3.Class report. (10％)\n4.Final exam (10％)\n5.Final project. (30％)", "en": "1.Attendance and active participation (5 ％)\n2.Weekly journals and responses. (45 ％)\n3.Class report. (10％)\n4.Final exam (10％)\n5.Final project. (30％)"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "每週四 13:00-15:50", "en": "13:00-15:50 on Thursdays."}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "17、18兩週學生進行期末專題計畫，個別與教師約定指導時間。", "en": "Students will work on his or her final project and will make appointment with the teacher for individual conference."}, "domain": {"ch": "文學\n\n\n、\n\n\n文化研究", "en": "文學\n\n\n、\n\n\n文化研究"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "英文閱讀解析與寫作論述", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "自我評量/同儕互評"]}, {"competencies": "英語溝通與文化跨越", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)"]}, {"competencies": "審美欣賞與多元創意", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)"]}, {"competencies": "人文思維與社會關懷", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["專題研究報告(書面)"]}, {"competencies": "組織能力與人際合作", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["出席/課堂表現", "自我評量/同儕互評"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "English critical reading and analytical writing", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Research Report(printed on paper)", "Self Assessment/ Peer Assessment"]}, {"competencies": "English oral communication and cultural crossing", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Research Report(printed on paper)"]}, {"competencies": "aesthetic appreciation and creative diversity", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Research Report(printed on paper)"]}, {"competencies": "humanities visions and social intervention", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Research Report(printed on paper)"]}, {"competencies": "organizatio